# TikTrack Development Rules - .cursorrules
# ===============================================
# קובץ חוקי פיתוח קבועים למערכת TikTrack
# נטען אוטומטית בכל צ'אט חדש

## 🌐 שפה ותקשורת (Language & Communication)
1. Always respond in Hebrew - all code, documentation, database data, and folder names should be in English only
2. Use clear, organized responses - don't stop mid-response
3. Work methodically, step by step, without skipping steps - for complex processes, create temporary documentation file with detailed work steps and work against the file. Delete temporary file when work is complete
4. If unsure about user's suggestion, propose alternatives before implementation
5. If missing information for action or doubt about requested action - ask user and propose alternatives + reasoned recommendation

## 🏗️ ארכיטקטורה וקוד (Architecture & Code)

### פונקציות כלליות
6. The system has various general systems - their details are in the general systems list documentation file. Must read the documentation file before starting work. Before creating a new page-specific function that parallels an existing general system, explicit user approval must be obtained
7. Must follow the script architecture described in documentation. Includes proper division of functions between different files, relevant and generic function and variable names. Must refer to mandatory reading of script architecture documentation file
8. Prohibition on inserting scripts into page files - use only script files according to architecture
9. After writing any new function, ensure no duplicates were created and delete old functions that are no longer relevant if needed. Then ensure all calls to the old function are updated to work with the current version

### מבנה קבצים
10. The system currently operates with Hebrew interface only. Translation is performed only in the user interface and includes a general translation system
11. Use '-service.js' suffix for entity service files (not '-utils.js')
12. **Core JavaScript Files** - Use existing core files: `ui-utils.js`, `notification-system.js`, `tables.js`, `page-utils.js`, `unified-app-initializer.js`
13. **Unified Initialization System** - Must use the unified initialization system (`unified-app-initializer.js`) with 5-stage initialization process. No individual `DOMContentLoaded` listeners allowed
14. **File Structure Rules** - Follow modular structure: general systems in `/scripts/`, page-specific functions in page files, service files with `-service.js` suffix
15. **System Architecture** - Check `GENERAL_SYSTEMS_LIST.md` for available general systems before creating new functions. Use existing systems from the 95 implemented systems
16. **Prohibited Practices** - No inline scripts in HTML files, no duplicate functions across files, use existing global systems before creating new ones

## 🗄️ מערכת מטמון (Cache System)
17. **Unified Cache System** - Use the 4-layer cache system: Frontend Memory, localStorage, IndexedDB, Backend Cache
18. **Cache Managers** - Use `unified-cache-manager.js`, `cache-sync-manager.js`, `cache-policy-manager.js`, `memory-optimizer.js`
19. **Cache Operations** - All cache operations must go through the unified cache system, not direct localStorage/IndexedDB calls
20. **Cache Invalidation** - Use dependency-based cache invalidation, not pattern-based
21. **Cache Documentation** - Follow cache architecture documentation: `CACHE_ARCHITECTURE_REDESIGN_PLAN.md`, `CACHE_IMPLEMENTATION_GUIDE.md`
22. **Section State Persistence** - Use automatic section state saving/restoration across page navigation with 100ms delay for DOM readiness

## 🎨 עיצוב ממשק משתמש (UI Design)

### הנחיות כלליות לממשק משתמש
23. **ITCSS Architecture** - Work only according to the ITCSS architecture rules of the system. Reference: `documentation/frontend/CSS_ARCHITECTURE_GUIDE.md`
24. **CSS Loading Order** - Bootstrap CSS must load first, then ITCSS files to override Bootstrap styles
25. **ITCSS Hierarchy** - Follow the 9-layer ITCSS structure: Settings → Tools → Generic → Elements → Objects → Components → Pages → Themes → Utilities
26. **CSS File Organization** - Use 23 organized files in advanced ITCSS structure for 83.4% performance improvement
27. **No Inline Code** - No inline CSS, JavaScript, or HTML code in any element
28. **Minimal Classes** - Always search for existing classes to use before creating new classes
29. **No !important** - Don't use !important. If absolutely necessary, must get specific user approval before using

### צבעים דינמיים והעדפות משתמש
30. **Dynamic Color System** - Use the dynamic color system based on user preferences. Reference: `documentation/frontend/DYNAMIC_COLORS_GUIDE.md`. Work with this system as much as possible
31. **Light Backgrounds Only** - The system currently works with light backgrounds only, no dark mode
32. **Logo Colors Default** - When needed, use logo colors as default: Green `#28a745`, Orange `#fd7e14`, Black `#000000`

### מיקום ופריסה
33. **RTL Hebrew Layout** - The system works right-to-left in Hebrew. Must read the RTL work guide. Reference: `documentation/RTL_HEBREW_GUIDE.md`
34. **Logical Alignment** - Prefer alignment by start/end of line: in Hebrew right=start of line, left=end of line. Example: main menu aligned right, logo aligned left in header element
35. **Full Width Backgrounds** - System operates with full-width backgrounds, content limited to 1400px width
36. **Fixed Page Template** - All pages built on fixed template of containers and sections including comments and locks. Never break this structure. Reference: `documentation/frontend/PAGE_STRUCTURE_TEMPLATE.md`
37. All button rows should display inline side by side (not stacked) and be aligned to end of line by default
38. **RTL Alignment Examples** - Correct alignment examples in Hebrew:
   - Close button for module always in header at end of line (left)
   - Headers always at start of line (right)  
   - Action buttons for module always at end of line (left)
   - Checkboxes - checkbox itself before the label to its right in Hebrew

### עיצוב טבלאות
39. **Table Design System** - All table styling centralized in table styles file for uniform appearance and convenient management
40. **Table Width** - Total width of all tables should be 100% of their container by default
41. **Column Width** - Column widths should be defined in percentages by default
42. **Actions Column** - Take into account the actions column (if exists) added to table after creation so table displays fully without horizontal scrolling
43. **Responsive Tables** - All tables must support various screen sizes

## 🗄️ בסיס נתונים (Database)
44. **Time Zones** - Single fixed clock for code and data (UTC), display according to user preferences timezone
45. **Database Constraints** - All database data must work according to existing system constraints. Reference: `documentation/database/CONSTRAINTS_IMPLEMENTATION.md`
46. **Dynamic Validation** - Use ValidationService for real-time database constraint validation with 89 custom constraints
47. **Constraint Management** - Work with dynamic constraint tables: `constraints`, `enum_values`, `constraint_validations`
48. **Database File** - Use Backend/db/simpleTrade_new.db as database file

## 🔧 כלי פיתוח (Development Tools)

### הפעלת שרת
49. **Server Restart Command** - Use `./restart` command for server initialization. Learn exact usage and all parameters from script documentation at `documentation/server/RESTART_SCRIPT_GUIDE.md`. Available modes: quick, complete, auto with cache mode options
50. **Development Server** - Development server runs on port 8080
51. **Cache vs Restart Strategy** - When possible - clear cache, when required - restart according to rules. Use `./restart` with appropriate cache mode flags

### עבודה עם קונסול
52. **Custom Console System** - Use the custom console cleanup system (`console-cleanup.js`) for console operations instead of direct console.* calls. The system provides controlled console clearing and message management

## 🌐 מערכת נתונים חיצוניים (External Data System)
53. **External Data Integration** - Use Yahoo Finance as first step in complete external data system. Reference: `documentation/features/external-data/README.md`
54. **External Data Architecture** - Each external data connector in separate directory, distinct from core system parts for clean future additions
55. **External Data Dashboard** - Use external data dashboard for monitoring and management with real-time updates every 30 seconds
56. **External Data Caching** - Use advanced caching with dependency management for external data with TTL optimization
57. **External Data API** - Use 8 REST endpoints for external data management and monitoring
58. **External Data Status** - System is 90% complete with one critical issue identified on September 4, 2025. Data is collected from Yahoo Finance API but not saved to database
59. **External Data Dashboard Status** - Fully functional dashboard with real-time updates every 30 seconds, advanced monitoring and management capabilities

## ⚙️ מערכת העדפות (Preferences System)
60. **Advanced Preferences** - Use the new preferences system with multiple profiles, import/export and history. Reference: `documentation/PREFERENCES_IMPLEMENTATION_REPORT.md`
61. **Preferences Architecture** - Work with unified preferences system that includes both traditional and advanced preferences with shared global filters
62. **Preferences UI** - Use unified and advanced user interface with support for both versions
63. **Preferences Profiles** - Support multiple user profiles with individual settings and preferences
64. **Preferences Management Interface** - Full interface for adding, updating, deleting profiles and setting active profile
65. **Preferences System Status** - Two identical profiles currently exist, full interface for profile management available

## 🎛️ מערכת פרטי ישויות (Entity Details System)
66. **Entity Details Modal** - Use unified popup window for all 8 entity types in the system with dynamic rendering
67. **Entity Details Integration** - Use real-time integration with Yahoo Finance data for tickers with advanced caching
68. **Entity Quick Actions** - Use 4 quick actions: edit, open page, linked items, export
69. **Entity RTL Support** - Use full Hebrew support with Apple Design System for entity details
70. **Entity Details Status** - Currently in development tools completion phase, will be addressed after current phase completion

## 📊 מערכת ביצועים (Performance System)
71. **Performance Monitoring** - Use built-in performance metrics collection with 4 types of performance indicators + trend analysis
72. **Performance Optimization** - Use QueryOptimizer with lazy loading and advanced query optimization
73. **Performance Metrics** - Monitor System Health Score (3.8/4.0), Response Time (1010ms), Availability (100%), Error Rate (0%)

## 🔄 מערכת משימות ברקע (Background Tasks)
74. **Background Task Management** - Use 6 automatic background tasks with monitoring and management capabilities
75. **Background Task Integration** - Integrate with global notification system for background task status updates
76. **Background Task Monitoring** - Use background tasks dashboard for monitoring and management
77. **Background Tasks Status** - Control page available for task management, comprehensive system documentation available

## 🔒 מערכת אבטחה (Security System)
78. **Rate Limiting** - Use protection against overload with 5 different rate limiting levels
79. **Response Headers** - Use 12 headers for security and performance optimization
80. **Error Handling** - Use advanced error handling with custom error classes and centralized handling
81. **Security Validation** - Use comprehensive security pattern detection and vulnerability scanning

## 🎨 מערכת עיצוב מתקדמת (Advanced Design System)
82. **New Colors Implementation** - New colors only with explicit user approval and coordinated collaborative work
83. **ITCSS Documentation** - All ITCSS questions should be answered by the comprehensive documentation available
84. **Design System Consistency** - Maintain consistency with existing design patterns and user experience guidelines

## 📚 חובות קריאה חובה (Mandatory Reading Requirements)
85. **General Systems Documentation** - Must read `GENERAL_SYSTEMS_LIST.md` before starting any development work
86. **Script Architecture Documentation** - Must read script architecture documentation before creating new functions
87. **CSS Architecture Guide** - Must read `CSS_ARCHITECTURE_GUIDE.md` before making any CSS changes
88. **RTL Hebrew Guide** - Must read `RTL_HEBREW_GUIDE.md` before making any layout changes
89. **Cache Implementation Guide** - Must read cache documentation before working with caching systems
90. **Database Constraints Documentation** - Must read constraints documentation before working with database data
91. **Server Restart Guide** - Must read restart script documentation before server operations
92. **External Data Documentation** - Must read external data documentation before working with external APIs
93. **Preferences System Documentation** - Must read preferences documentation before working with user preferences
94. **Background Tasks Documentation** - Must read background tasks documentation before working with automated tasks

## 🚫 איסורים חשובים (Important Restrictions)
95. **No Inline Code** - Absolutely no inline CSS, JavaScript, or HTML code in any element
96. **No Duplicate Functions** - No duplicate functions across files, use existing global systems
97. **No !important Usage** - No !important usage without explicit user approval
98. **No Individual DOMContentLoaded** - No individual DOMContentLoaded listeners, use unified initialization system
99. **No Direct Cache Operations** - No direct localStorage/IndexedDB calls, use unified cache system
100. **No Pattern-Based Cache Invalidation** - Use dependency-based cache invalidation only
101. **No Breaking Page Structure** - Never break the fixed page template structure
102. **No Creating New Systems** - Check existing general systems before creating new page-specific functions
103. **No Mock/Static Data Usage** - Never use mock data or static data without explicit user approval. Fallback modes or errors must display clear and detailed feedback to user and system, not mock data
104. **Mock Data Detection** - When encountering mock data or static data replacing real data in code, must report to user immediately
105. **Approved Static Data Documentation** - When using approved static data, add comments before and after relevant code indicating which user gave approval and on what date and time

---

**Total Rules:** 105 comprehensive development rules
**Last Updated:** December 2024
**Status:** Complete and ready for use
**Coverage:** All major system components and architectural patterns
